# CARNALYSYS — project stack

## Monorepo

- **Backend:** `backend/` — Maven module `carnalysys-api`, base package `com.carnalysys`.
- **Frontend:** repo root `src/`, `index.html`, Vite — calls REST under `/api/v1`.

## REST API

- Controllers live under `com.carnalysys.web.v1` (e.g. `*V1Controller.java`).
- Responses often use a shared envelope pattern (`ApiEnvelope`, `ApiResponses.ok`).
- Public catalog vs admin vs user routes are separated; security filters apply per path (see `Security` config).

## Data

- JPA entities in `domain/`; repositories in `repo/`; Flyway migrations in `backend/src/main/resources/db/migration/`.
- Prefer schema changes via **new Flyway versions**, not ad-hoc DDL in code.

## When editing Java

- Match existing layering: **Controller → Service → Repository → Entity**.
- Use `@Transactional` on service methods that mutate or span multiple repository calls.
- Preserve existing DTO/envelope and error (`ApiException`) conventions.

## When editing React

- Prefer existing `services/*` and `api/client.js` over raw `fetch` scattered in components.
- Admin UI is under `src/admin/`; public store under `src/pages/` and `src/components/`.

## Optional deep rules

If symlinks from `scripts/link-cursor-java-rules.sh` are present, use **@** mentions on those files for Spring/Maven/architecture deep dives (e.g. `@302-frameworks-spring-boot-rest.mdc`).
